It is a user-trainable model mainly used for personalized and specialized pre-training of knowledge. It enables lifelong contextual learning for users, embedding and representing knowledge in vertical domains, effectively reducing AI counterfactuals in vertical applications, and providing continuously consistent and more controllable services. The goal is to achieve "responsible AI, trustworthy AI, and user-friendly AI." Based on this mega model, DeepBlue has developed products such as the Metamind app and the Silicon-based Brain SaaS platform. As an AI industrial ecology maker, DeepBlue Technology has made significant strides in various AI verticals since its founding in 2014. With a strong commitment to serving humanity through AI, DeepBlue has become a leader in intelligent driving, intelligent robots, intelligent industries, and intelligent health. DeepBlue Technology's success is underscored by its numerous accolades, including winning over 40 top-tier international competitions in computer science and AI, such as CVPR, ICCV, ECCV, ACL, NAACL, KDD, NeurIPS, and AAAI. The company's dedication to innovation and its focus on core technologies like computer vision, biological intelligence, autonomous driving, and cognitive intelligence have earned it recognition as a "little giant" enterprise by the Ministry of Industry and Information Technology. Now, DeepBlue Technology is thrilled to be a part of Interclean Amsterdam 2024, the world's largest professional cleaning trade fair. This event, scheduled for May 14th to 17th, promises to be bigger, better, and bolder than ever before. Interclean Amsterdam 2024 will bring together industry professionals from around the globe to explore the latest trends, products, and services in the cleaning and hygiene sector. With over 900 exhibitors, 11 exhibition halls, and an expected attendance of 30,000 visitors from 120+ countries, Interclean offers an unparalleled opportunity for networking, business development, and staying ahead of market developments. Attendees can look forward to engaging seminars hosted by industry experts, cutting-edge cleaning technologies and solutions, live demonstrations, and immersive trade show experiences. The event will also feature the new Interclean Social Club, offering live music, celebrity appearances, comedy acts, and other entertainment activities. For DeepBlue Technology, Interclean Amsterdam 2024 is not just a trade fair but a platform to showcase its innovative AI solutions for the cleaning and hygiene industry. Visitors can expect to discover groundbreaking insights and technologies that are revolutionizing the future of clean. We invite you to join DeepBlue Technology at Interclean Amsterdam 2024 and be part of this transformative event. Explore the latest in cleaning technologies, connect with industry leaders, and envision the future of clean and sustainable solutions. Don't miss out on this exceptional opportunity to experience the best that Interclean and DeepBlue Technology have to offer!
